Statement of Spokesman for AINDF on May Day 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front (AINDF) issued a statement on May 1, a holiday of the working people the world over, according to Internet site Kuguk Jonson.
 The working masses in the south of Korea are significantly greeting the 116th May Day, a holiday of the working people, at a time when the massive struggle for labor liberation is being waged more dynamically than ever before under the banner of national independence, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The working masses in this land have successfully discharged their responsibility and role as the main force of the movement for change in the rigorous and grim struggle to retake the sovereignty of the nation from the outside forces and achieve the genuine labor liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But they have not yet achieved labor liberation and class emancipation, their cherished desire, and the reunification of Korea, the supreme task of the nation.
 Workers and other working masses in the south have been mercilessly deprived of national sovereignty, democracy, people's right and vital rights due to the U.S. colonial domination over south Korea for over 60 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States is craftily scheming to bring back the dark period of the fascist dictatorship which ruthlessly violated the dignity and vital rights of the people including the working masses, while manipulating the "Grand National Party's" frantic moves to seize power. And it is keen to arrest the trend of the June 15 era toward national reconciliation, unity and reunification, while stepping up the reckless preparations for a war against the north to impose nuclear disasters upon the nation.
 The reality shows that the people can neither realize the dream of progressive reform nor expect triumphant advance of the June 15 era unless the U.S. domination is terminated and pro-U.S. traitorous forces removed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The working masses in this land should put an end to the disgraceful history of the U.S. occupation of south Korea, the root cause of all misfortune and sufferings of the nation.

Japan Urged Not to Turn Deaf Ear to Demand of Times 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Japan will find itself further disadvantaged, if it continues to deny and distort its past crimes, turning a deaf ear to the demand of the times, warns Rodong Sinmun in an article Tuesday.
 It is the demand of the public sentiments today not to connive at the crimes of the Japanese imperialists in their past aggression, especially their crimes in drafting "comfort women" for the Imperial Japanese Army and not to allow Japan to repeat those crimes through the settlement of its past, notes the author of the article, adding: The U.S. Congressional Research Service recently made public a report on the "comfort women" issue, which we may construe as one reflecting this trend of the times.
 The Japanese militarists do not so much as admit their crimes concerning the "comfort women," though it is past 60 years since their defeat, but are shameless enough to distort the fact, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have not yet shaken off their past dream of aggression. It is the ideological view deeply rooted in their minds to ride on the back of Korea and other Asian countries and rule them again. 
 The Japanese reactionaries are totally striking out materials about the "comfort women" for the Imperial Japanese Army from the history textbooks, driving for the revision of the "Pacifist Constitution" and massive bolstering of armed forces for aggression and coming out with the claim to Tok Islet. All these reveal their wild ambition for reinvasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those who refuse to admit their crimes and feel no responsibility for them are bound to repeat them or commit bigger crimes. Now Japan is behaving like this. The Japanese reactionaries are resorting to crafty tricks to play down and gloss away their past crimes and escape from the responsibility for them, peddling the ware of "abduction issue" which has already been settled. On the other hand, they are persisting in the anti-DPRK smear campaign and driving the DPRK-Japan hostile relations to the extremes under preposterous pretexts. Their negation of their past crimes and malicious hostile acts against the DPRK maximize the resentment of the Korean people against Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No illusion should be harbored about Japan. It is the unshakable will of the Korean people to count up the past crimes of Japan. The Korean people will regard as moves for the second invasion of Korea the Japanese reactionaries' distortion and total denial of the crimes of the Japanese imperialists in committing aggression on Korea including the "comfort women" issue and settle account with them up to the bitter end.

Joint Gathering of Working People on May Day 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- A joint gathering of working people in Pyongyang took place at the pleasure ground in Mt. Taesong on Monday to commemorate May Day.
 The gathering was attended by Kim Song Chol and Won Hyong Guk, vice-chairmen of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, and workers and union members of different factories and enterprises in Pyongyang.
 Present were a south Korean delegation of labor movement organizations jointly headed by Chief Vice-Chairman of the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions Yun Yong Gyu and Chief Vice-Chairman of the Federation of south Korean Trade Unions Yu Jae Sop, foreign guests and overseas Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun Sok Nam, chairman of the Pyongyang City Committee of the GFTUK, said that all the workers and union members should discharge their responsibility and role in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, holding high the red flag.
 He called for consolidating solidarity between workers in the north and the south and advancing hand in hand in implementing the June 15 joint declaration.
 Yu Jae Sop and Yun Yong Gyu called upon workers in the north and the south to take the lead in the movement for national reunification, saying that all the fellow countrymen should achieve independence, peace and great unity of the nation for the reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then a performance was given by artistes of the State National Art Troupe.
 The repertoire of the performance, which began with chorus "General Kim Il Sung Is Our Sun", included chorus "Song of May Day", female folk solo "Only One Mind", Kayagum ensemble "Let's Sing of Our Pride in Being under the Guidance of the General", dance "Dancing with Janggo" and mixed duet "Arirang for Reunification".
 And there were sports and amusement games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rhythmic exercise and Taekwon-do for health were performed first.
 Then participants were divided into "Taesongsan" and "Taedonggang" teams and held colorful sports and amusement games including Korean map-puzzle, running with a ball between foreheads and a tug of war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the games surged into high tide, workers of the north and the south ran and ran together with a single mind to take the lead in the struggle to achieve national reunification, the cherished desire of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When series of songs of reunification, "Let's Meet Again" and other wind music pieces were played by the women's brass band of the Ministry of People's Security, all the participants responded with applause.

Japan Urged to Behave Itself 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) --Japanese reactionaries are vying with each other to vociferate about the "abduction issue" these days. This comes under fire by a signed commentary of Minju Joson today.
  It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Some days ago, Chief Cabinet Secretary Abe asserted that "Japan is standing for the settlement of the abduction issue on the basis of the fundamental way of thinking supported by dialogue and pressure" and "it is necessary to increase the pressure upon north Korea". Japanese Foreign Minister Aso also solicited this or that country for cooperation in the efforts to settle the "abduction issue". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Presumably, the "abduction issue" is regarded as a yardstick estimating the ability, qualification and popularity of politicians in the political camp of Japan. The reason can be explained by the fact that the tricksters seized by the greed for power going under the masks of politicians consider the "abduction issue" as something useful for achieving their sinister political purpose and have deliberately hyped up it to this end.
 As already known, the "abduction issue" had already found its settlement thanks to the sincere approach and efforts of the DPRK government. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the calculation of the Japanese reactionaries that should they deem the "abduction issue" as settled, this will mean losing a justification for having used it as an important lever for wresting power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By stepping up their policy of pressure upon the DPRK over the "abduction issue" they seek to gain popularity among Japanese and garner their support and come to power come what may. 
 The DPRK does not care whether they are locked in a factional or sectarian strife for the assumption of power. However, the DPRK will never allow them to persistently use the "abduction issue" for their smear campaign against it while engaging themselves in a scramble for power over. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is still abducting citizens of the DPRK in the area bordering on China in broad daylight, not yet away from its bad habit of abducting people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will certainly force the Japanese reactionaries to pay dearly for all the crimes Japan committed against it including the "abduction issue". 
 The DPRK urges Japan once again to behave itself with reason.

Solar Heat Widely Used in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- A great effort has been channeled into the work of effectively using solar heat in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Many solar factories, greenhouses and fish farms have been built in recent years.
 In Haeju City, South Hwanghae Province, more than 90 solar Hukbosan fertilizer factories have newly been constructed. They save 50 percent of fuel compared with the existing Hukbosan fertilizer factories. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thousands of solar greenhouse buildings have mushroomed in different parts of the country in a few years. Industrial establishments and rural communities are constructing solar vegetable greenhouses of various sizes and shapes to suit their actual conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koksan County Food Administration in North Hwanghae Province produces ten kinds of vegetables with only solar heat in a greenhouse covering some 410 square meters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A laboratory of an educational institution has built a solar fish farm, where it is engaged in researches into breeding freshwater fishes and is raising fry.
 The walls of the fish farm are under the ground except the light-accepting plane, so its heat loss is low and indoor temperature ensured well. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The farm is also breeding ornamental fishes including goldfish, Lebistes reticulatus.
